A poison ring or pillbox ring is a type of ring with a container under the bezel or inside the bezel itself that could be used to hold poison or another substance. They became popular in Europe during the sixteenth century. The poison ring was used either to slip poison into an enemy's food or drink, or to facilitate the suicide of the wearer in order to escape capture or torture.
Rings like this have been used throughout history to carry perfume, locks of hair, devotional relics, messages and other keepsakes, so they have also been known by other names. Artists would paint tiny portraits of loved ones, to be carried in what was called a “locket ring,” which was popular during the Renaissance. By the 17th century, jewelers were creating locket rings in the shape of caskets which served as mementos for mourners. These were called “funeral rings.” Rings with compartments are also called “box” rings or “socket” ring

Product name: Art Deco Engagement Ring, Pave Ribbon Shoulder, Sterling Silver Ring, Milgrain Detail, 1930s Engagement Ring, Unique Vargas? Art Deco Ring.
Description:
Art Deco Engagement Ring, Pave Ribbon Shoulder, Sterling Silver Ring, Milgrain Detail, 1930s Engagement Ring, Unique Vargas? Art Deco Ring.
If you are looking for an engagement ring that is not like anyone else's this is the ring for you.  This beautiful Antique Art Deco Engagement Ring has 23 stones total, starting with a crystal clear, beautifully cut stone set in a raised basket mounting with milgrain detail on the corners.  On the shoulders you have a "ribbon" of 11 prong set clear stones on either side of the main stone.  This ribbon piece is attache to the and just where the band begins to round up to the top and rises up to where the top of the stone sits in the basket mounting, giving the appearance from the top that the stone is set down into a ribbon flowing underneath it.  A striking top view that you will just love, and love to show off.  The band is a nice 1/8" wide all the way around, making this a very comfortable ring to wear.  
 
The ring is in excellent vintage condition with all of the stones securely in place.  It is marked STERLING at the back of the band.  There are no other markings on the ring, but I believe this may be an early Vargas, as I have seen early Vargas designs with attached side pieces like this one.
The ring is a size 7.  The main stone measures 7mm.  The mounting measures 7/8" square at the top.  The ring measures 1/2" at the top of the shoulder piece and 3/8" at the bottom of the side piece.  The ring sits 1/4" high.  The band is 1/8" wide all around.
The ring will be shipped in a ring box.

Product name: FSL Flower, Free Standing Lace Flower Embroidery Design, In the Hoop Flower, Large Embroidery Flower, 3D Embroidery , Summer Flower
Description:
FSL Flower Embroidery Design complete with clear instructions for a large 3D Embroidery Flower. This flower is created with water soluble stabiliser. The flower's petals are all completed in the hoop. Then just join the petals using a glue gun or the traditional needle and thread. Full instructions on PDF are included when you download the file. 
The finished flower measures approximately 5 inches in diameter. All the petals are created in 2 hoopings. There is only 1 colour change in the second hoop, so although the pattern takes a bit of time to stitch out, it is very simple and the machine will not need your TLC while stitching out. 
{You may leave it unattended :) }
Stitch counts : Hoop A: 19676, Hoop B: 23763
At the moment the design is only available for 5x7 hoops but 4x4 will be coming up shortly. More FSL flowers will also be added in time for Summer.
Once purchased, you will be able to download 1 compressed file which contains the same design in the following formats:
.CSD
.DST
.EXP
.HUS
.JEF
.PES
.VIP
.XXX
.VP3
This listing does NOT include a physical embroidered character. This is a pattern for an embroidery machine. Transfer the file you require to your machine using a pen drive or using the cable that came with the machine.
Kindly respect my work. You may sell the embroidered item or anything else that you produce with this pattern, but you may not resell the pattern, transfer it, share it or distribute it, in any way. You may not share this design on Social Media sites, Blogs or in any other way, for free or at a profit.
